    "From Table 5, it can be seen that our proposed method BCNN-CWS in general achieves the best results for the experiments in all the cases.",
    "This indicates that our proposed method can effectively solve the low-resource problem.",
    "Ablation experimentEffects of the joint training mechanism with CWS.",
    "We conduct an ablation experiment for the CWS module to verify the contributions of the main components of our model to the performance of the entity recognition task.",
    "According to the sequence labeling underlying both NER and CWS tasks, our model, BCNN-CWS, uses CWS as the auxiliary task and defines a multitask learning framework to generate hidden representations adequately for entity recognition."
